---
import CardGrid from '../../components/CardGrid.astro';
import RuleCallout from '../../components/RuleCallout.astro';
import ContentLayout from '../../layouts/ContentLayout.astro';
---

<ContentLayout
  title="Character Creation"
  summary="Build a wanderer from any world, bind them to a ka-tet, and set them on the Path of the Beam."
  eyebrow="Player creation"
  audience="player"
  ctaPrimary={{ label: 'View Archetypes', href: '/player-guide/archetypes' }}
  ctaSecondary={{ label: 'Download Character Sheet', href: '/downloads/character-sheet.md' }}
>
  <section class="section content-prose">
    <p class="content-lead">
      This page is the player-facing source of truth for creating a Ka-Tet character. It should
      help a new player make a usable character without needing to understand the entire rulebook
      first.
    </p>
  </section>

  <RuleCallout
    title="Quick Summary"
    points={[
      'Choose your character concept and world of origin.',
      'Choose your archetype.',
      'Assign your ability scores.',
      'Choose your background, ethos, gear, and personal scar.',
      'Calculate your derived stats.',
      'Choose your starting features, powers, and equipment.',
      'Write your ka-tet bond.',
      'Finish your backstory and review the character with the GM.',
    ]}
  />

  <section class="split">
    <div class="section content-prose">
      <p class="section-label">Starting Level Guidance</p>
      <p>
        Most new campaigns should start at <strong>Level 1</strong> or <strong>Level 3</strong>.
        For demos, convention games, and shop-table one-shots, <strong>Level 3 is recommended</strong>{' '}
        because characters have enough identity to feel distinct without becoming difficult to run.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div class="section content-prose">
      <p class="section-label">Core Reminder</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Start with the person, not the numbers.</li>
        <li>Every character needs a scar.</li>
        <li>The party is a ka-tet, not a stack of solo heroes.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section content-prose">
    <p class="section-label">What You Need On Your Sheet</p>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Character Sheet Field</th>
          <th>What It Means</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Character Name</td><td>Your name, nickname, alias, or title.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Player Name</td><td>The player running the character.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Level</td><td>Your current character level.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Archetype</td><td>Your class and core role in the story.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Subclass / Path</td><td>Your specialization, usually chosen at Level 3.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>World of Origin</td><td>The world, time, and reality your character came from.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Background</td><td>Who you were before ka pulled you onto the road.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Ethos</td><td>Your moral compass: White, Gray, or Red.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Ability Scores</td><td>Strength, Dexterity, Constitution, Intelligence, Wisdom, and Charisma.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Grit / HP</td><td>Your ability to endure harm, exhaustion, and violence.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Armor Class</td><td>How hard you are to hit in combat.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Proficiency Bonus</td><td>Your level-based training bonus.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Saving Throws / Skills</td><td>What you are trained to resist and do well.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Attacks / Powers</td><td>Weapons, attacks, spells, songs, or tech abilities.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Equipment</td><td>Weapons, armor, relics, supplies, tools, and keepsakes.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Ka Points</td><td>Your pool of fate, luck, and narrative force.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Personal Scar</td><td>The wound that follows you into the story.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Ka-Tet Bond</td><td>Your connection to another PC and why ka bound you together.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Backstory</td><td>A short summary of who you were before the campaign began.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section class="section content-prose">
    <p class="section-label">Step 1: Choose A Character Concept</p>
    <p>Ask yourself:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Who were you before the Tower called?</li>
      <li>What world, age, or reality did you come from?</li>
      <li>What did ka take from you?</li>
      <li>What do you still want?</li>
      <li>Why would you risk your life for strangers?</li>
      <li>What part of you is already broken?</li>
      <li>What part of you refuses to die?</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Characters in Ka-Tet can come from almost anywhere. The Dark Tower touches all worlds, and
      ka gathers people from many wheres and whens.
    </p>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Origin</th>
          <th>Character Possibilities</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Mid-World</td><td>Fallen gunslinger, Calla farmer, Manni pilgrim, harrier deserter, or Lud scavenger.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Keystone Earth</td><td>Runaway, detective, musician, soldier, addict, teacher, preacher, hacker, or ordinary person with impossible dreams.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Old Gilead</td><td>Failed apprentice, exiled knight, battlefield survivor, or gunslinger-in-training.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Thunderclap</td><td>Breaker escapee, psychic prisoner, Low Man defector, or machine-haunted survivor.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Lud</td><td>Tunnel orphan, tech scavenger, Grays deserter, or half-mad machine prophet.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Future Earth</td><td>Cyberpunk assassin, AI technician, wasteland medic, drone pilot, or corporate fugitive.</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Ancient Earth</td><td>Monk, prophet, soldier, witch, Viking, gladiator, or court singer touched by the Beam.</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p><strong>Concept formula:</strong></p>
    <p>
      <em>
        I am a [background] from [world/time] who was [wounded, changed, exiled, chosen, hunted,
        or saved] by [event]. Now I follow the Beam because [reason], but I fear [truth].
      </em>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section content-prose">
    <p class="section-label">Step 2: Choose An Archetype</p>
    <p>
      Your archetype is your class. It defines your core role, combat style, special abilities,
      hit die, primary stats, saving throws, and starting features.
    </p>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Archetype</th>
          <th>Core Fantasy</th>
          <th>Best For</th>
          <th>Common Primary Stats</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Gunslinger</td><td>Knight-errant with revolvers and a brutal code</td><td>Duel, protect the tet, lead under pressure</td><td>Dexterity, Wisdom</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Walker</td><td>Traveler between doors, thinnies, and worlds</td><td>Teleport, scout, manipulate space</td><td>Dexterity, Wisdom, Intelligence</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Singer</td><td>Voice of the Beam through song and resonance</td><td>Support, heal, calm horror, shape emotion</td><td>Charisma, Wisdom</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Tech-Knight</td><td>Old Ones tech scavenger and engineer</td><td>Use gadgets, repair systems, wear tech armor</td><td>Intelligence, Dexterity</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Demon-Blooded</td><td>Human soul carrying Prim-born or demonic power</td><td>Fight with corruption and dark force</td><td>Charisma, Constitution</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Touch-Bearer</td><td>Psychic, empath, seer, or dream-touched wanderer</td><td>Read danger, glimpse fate, protect through intuition</td><td>Wisdom, Charisma</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Hemophage</td><td>Blood-hungry predator or cursed survivor</td><td>Feed, stalk, regenerate, struggle with hunger</td><td>Dexterity, Constitution</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Protocol Shell</td><td>Construct or android with a soul-shaped glitch</td><td>Play a machine becoming more than code</td><td>Intelligence, Dexterity</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Tongue of Discord</td><td>Manipulator, false prophet, coercive speaker</td><td>Bend truth, deceive, command, terrify</td><td>Charisma, Intelligence</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Shard-Bound</td><td>Fractured soul with multiple selves</td><td>Shift personas and survive identity horror</td><td>Wisdom, Charisma, Constitution</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>
      Most archetypes choose a subclass, path, discipline, or resonance at <strong>Level 3</strong>.
      If your campaign starts at Level 3, choose it during character creation.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section content-prose">
    <p class="section-label">Step 3: Assign Ability Scores</p>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Ability</th>
          <th>What It Measures</th>
          <th>Common Uses</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Strength</td><td>Physical power and brutal leverage</td><td>Melee attacks, climbing, forcing doors, grappling</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Dexterity</td><td>Agility, reflexes, aim, balance</td><td>Firearms, stealth, initiative, finesse</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Constitution</td><td>Endurance and bodily resilience</td><td>Grit, poison, disease, exhaustion, harsh travel</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Intelligence</td><td>Knowledge, reasoning, technical skill</td><td>Old Ones tech, investigation, lore, engineering</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Wisdom</td><td>Perception, instinct, spiritual sensitivity</td><td>Insight, survival, resisting fear, sensing the Beam</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Charisma</td><td>Presence, leadership, force of soul</td><td>Persuasion, performance, command, prophecy</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>
      Recommended method: start all six scores at <strong>8</strong> and spend <strong>27 points</strong>.
      You cannot raise a score above <strong>15</strong> before bonuses.
    </p>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Final Score</th>
          <th>Point Cost</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>8</td><td>0</td></tr>
        <tr><td>9</td><td>1</td></tr>
        <tr><td>10</td><td>2</td></tr>
        <tr><td>11</td><td>3</td></tr>
        <tr><td>12</td><td>4</td></tr>
        <tr><td>13</td><td>5</td></tr>
        <tr><td>14</td><td>7</td></tr>
        <tr><td>15</td><td>9</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Build Type</th>
          <th>Scores Before Bonuses</th>
          <th>Best For</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Focused Hero</td><td>15, 15, 15, 8, 8, 8</td><td>Specialized characters with clear weaknesses</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Balanced Adventurer</td><td>15, 14, 13, 12, 10, 8</td><td>Recommended default</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Broad Survivor</td><td>14, 14, 13, 12, 10, 10</td><td>Skill-heavy or roleplay-heavy characters</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Jack-of-All-Worlds</td><td>13, 13, 13, 12, 12, 12</td><td>Strange or broad concepts</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p><strong>Fast alternate method:</strong> 15, 14, 13, 12, 10, 8.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="section content-prose">
    <p class="section-label">Step 4: Choose Background, Ethos, Gear, And Scar</p>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Background</th>
          <th>Description</th>
          <th>Possible Benefits</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Exiled Knight of Gilead</td><td>Trained under a fallen code, cast out or left behind</td><td>Firearms, History, Intimidation, Survival</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Calla Farmer</td><td>Borderland survivor from a threatened village</td><td>Animal Handling, Survival, Athletics</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Traveler from New York</td><td>Pulled from Keystone Earth or a nearby level of reality</td><td>Persuasion, Streetwise, History</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Thunderclap Escapee</td><td>Former prisoner, Breaker, or witness of the Red’s machinery</td><td>Insight, psychic lore, Stealth</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Choir Runaway</td><td>Your voice had power, and someone tried to own it</td><td>Performance, Insight, Persuasion</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Road Medic</td><td>You learned to stitch wounds in bad places</td><td>Medicine, Survival, medical tools</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <h3>Ethos</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>White:</strong> Serve creation, mercy, truth, sacrifice, or the Beam.</li>
      <li><strong>Gray:</strong> Survive, protect your own, and choose case by case.</li>
      <li><strong>Red:</strong> Seek power, corruption, cruelty, or Discordia.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Personal Scar Examples</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>A bullet wound that aches near thinnies</li>
      <li>A song you cannot stop humming</li>
      <li>A dead sibling who appears in mirrors</li>
      <li>A memory you gave away and cannot recover</li>
      <li>A voice in your head that sounds like you, but older</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Every Character Should Begin With</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>One primary weapon or focus</li>
      <li>One backup weapon or defensive tool</li>
      <li>Travel clothes or armor</li>
      <li>Basic supplies for the road</li>
      <li>One personal keepsake</li>
      <li>Any tools granted by archetype or background</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="section content-prose">
    <p class="section-label">Step 5: Calculate Derived Stats</p>
    <h3>Ability Modifiers</h3>
    <p><strong>Modifier = floor((Ability Score - 10) / 2)</strong></p>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Ability Score</th>
          <th>Modifier</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>8–9</td><td>-1</td></tr>
        <tr><td>10–11</td><td>+0</td></tr>
        <tr><td>12–13</td><td>+1</td></tr>
        <tr><td>14–15</td><td>+2</td></tr>
        <tr><td>16–17</td><td>+3</td></tr>
        <tr><td>18–19</td><td>+4</td></tr>
        <tr><td>20–21</td><td>+5</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <h3>Grit / HP</h3>
    <p><strong>Level 1 Grit = Archetype Hit Die maximum + Constitution modifier</strong></p>
    <h3>Proficiency Bonus</h3>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Level</th>
          <th>Bonus</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>1–4</td><td>+2</td></tr>
        <tr><td>5–8</td><td>+3</td></tr>
        <tr><td>9–12</td><td>+4</td></tr>
        <tr><td>13–16</td><td>+5</td></tr>
        <tr><td>17–20</td><td>+6</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <h3>Armor Class</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Unarmored:</strong> 10 + Dexterity modifier</li>
      <li><strong>Armored:</strong> Armor value + Dexterity modifier, unless stated otherwise</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Ka Points</h3>
    <p>
      Most characters begin with <strong>1 Ka Point</strong>, hold a maximum of{' '}
      <strong>3</strong>, and refresh to <strong>1</strong> at the start of a session if empty.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Reroll a d20 after seeing the result</li>
      <li>Spend 2 Ka to turn catastrophe into survival, with GM approval</li>
      <li>Ask the GM for a stroke of luck, clue, or narrow escape</li>
      <li>Donate 1 Ka to another member of the ka-tet when the bond justifies it</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="section content-prose">
    <p class="section-label">Step 6: Choose Starting Features, Powers, And Equipment</p>
    <p>At minimum, record:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Hit Die and primary stats</li>
      <li>Saving throw proficiencies and skill choices</li>
      <li>Weapon and armor proficiencies</li>
      <li>Level 1 archetype features</li>
      <li>Any spellcasting, powers, charges, blood reserve, or similar resource system</li>
      <li>Starting weapons, armor, tools, supplies, and subclass choice if starting at Level 3+</li>
    </ul>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Starting Level</th>
          <th>Why Use It</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>1</td><td>Fragile origin-story play</td></tr>
        <tr><td>2</td><td>Characters who already survived one major ordeal</td></tr>
        <tr><td>3</td><td>Best default for demos and public games</td></tr>
        <tr><td>5</td><td>Experienced groups or cinematic one-shots</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section class="section content-prose">
    <p class="section-label">Step 7: Create Your Ka-Tet Bond</p>
    <p>
      The party is not just a group of adventurers. It is a ka-tet: one made from many. Every
      character should define at least one bond with another PC.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Which member of the ka-tet saved your life?</li>
      <li>Which member do you not fully trust, and why?</li>
      <li>Which member reminds you of someone you lost?</li>
      <li>Which member knows a secret you wish they did not?</li>
      <li>Which member do you believe ka wants you to protect?</li>
      <li>Which member might one day be forced to kill you?</li>
    </ul>
    <h3>Khef Exercise</h3>
    <ol>
      <li>What did your character contribute to the group's survival before the campaign began?</li>
      <li>What does your character rely on another member of the ka-tet for?</li>
    </ol>
  </section>

  <section class="section content-prose">
    <p class="section-label">Step 8: Finish Your Backstory</p>
    <p>
      A good starting backstory is <strong>one to three paragraphs</strong> and answers:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Where are you from?</li>
      <li>What did you lose?</li>
      <li>What do you want?</li>
      <li>What do you fear?</li>
      <li>What strange thing marked you?</li>
      <li>Why are you willing to walk with this ka-tet?</li>
      <li>What would tempt you away from the Beam?</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Backstory template:</strong></p>
    <p>
      <em>
        [Name] came from [world/time/place], where they lived as [background]. Their life changed
        when [inciting event]. Since then, they have carried [scar, secret, relic, guilt, curse,
        or memory]. They follow the Beam because [motivation], but they fear [inner truth]. Their
        bond with the ka-tet began when [shared survival moment].
      </em>
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section content-prose">
    <p class="section-label">Example Character Creation</p>
    <h2>Naomi Blueglass</h2>
    <p>
      Naomi Blueglass is a runaway choir singer from 1977 Keystone Earth. She heard a second voice
      beneath her own during a church solo, and that voice whispered the names of worlds she had
      never seen.
    </p>
    <table>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Ability</th>
          <th>Score</th>
          <th>Modifier</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Strength</td><td>8</td><td>-1</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Dexterity</td><td>12</td><td>+1</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Constitution</td><td>13</td><td>+1</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Intelligence</td><td>10</td><td>+0</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Wisdom</td><td>14</td><td>+2</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Charisma</td><td>15</td><td>+2</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Background:</strong> Choir Runaway</li>
      <li><strong>Ethos:</strong> White, though she doubts herself</li>
      <li><strong>Personal Scar:</strong> Her throat glows faintly blue when thinnies are near</li>
      <li><strong>Starting Keepsake:</strong> A cracked church hymnal with one page that rewrites itself</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      Naomi Blueglass ran from a world that told her miracles belonged to men behind pulpits. Her
      voice broke glass, calmed animals, and made dying people smile. When a door opened in the
      back of an abandoned train station, she followed the hum through and woke beneath the wrong
      stars.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="split">
    <div class="section content-prose">
      <p class="section-label">Final Review Checklist</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Name, level, archetype, and subclass/path if applicable</li>
        <li>World of origin, background, and ethos</li>
        <li>Ability scores, modifiers, Grit/HP, AC, and proficiency bonus</li>
        <li>Saving throws, skills, attacks, gear, and Ka Points</li>
        <li>Archetype features, powers, charges, or songs if applicable</li>
        <li>Personal scar, ka-tet bond, and short backstory</li>
        <li>GM approval for unusual origins, relics, powers, or secrets</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="section content-prose">
      <p class="section-label">Common Mistakes</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Forgetting to add Constitution modifier to Grit/HP</li>
        <li>Choosing an archetype without a strong primary stat</li>
        <li>Forgetting Ka Points or proficiency bonus</li>
        <li>Writing a backstory so long the GM cannot use it</li>
        <li>Choosing gear without practical supplies</li>
        <li>Making a lone-wolf character with no reason to stay in the ka-tet</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

